
[1]remediless

   REMED'ILESS, a. [In modern books, the accent is placed on the first
   syllable, which would be well if there were no derivatives; but
   remedilessly, remedilessness, require the accent on the second
   syllable.]

   1. Not admitting a remedy; incurable; desperate; as a remediless
   disease.

   2. Irreparable; as, a loss or damage is remediless.

   3. Not admitting change or reversal; as a remediless doom.

   4. Not admitting recovery; as a remediless delusion.
